# MCP Servers (Cursor — generic)

MCP server definitions in `~/.cursor/mcp.json` apply **across all workspaces** on this machine. Prefer user-global MCP config over per-repo `.cursor/mcp.json` duplicates after promote.

Repo-specific server inventory and launcher paths live in project `mcp.instructions.md`.

## Agent discipline

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Read schema first | Inspect the MCP tool descriptor (parameters, required fields) before every `CallMcpTool` |
| Prefer MCP over shell | When a task matches an enabled MCP server, use MCP — not ad-hoc scripts or browser automation |
| Stateless tools | Many servers take an explicit `path` (or equivalent) per call — no session setup unless the server docs require it |
| Fail clearly | If MCP is missing or auth fails, say which server/tool failed; do not silently fall back to destructive file edits |
| Partial capability | If MCP cannot complete the request, finish what you can and report what was blocked |

## Configuration shape (stdio)

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "server-name": {
      "command": "/path/to/python",
      "args": ["/path/to/server.py"]
    }
  }
}
```

Multi-root workspaces may use `${workspaceFolder:<folderName>}` in `command` / `args` when the server lives in a named workspace folder.

## VS Code Copilot → Cursor tool mapping (MCP)

| Copilot / VS Code | Cursor |
|-------------------|--------|
| `knowledge-repo/*`, domain MCP tool namespaces | `CallMcpTool` against the matching server in `mcp.json` |
| `web/fetch` | `WebFetch` (only when MCP is not the right transport) |

## Promote workflow

1. `python -m ai.agent.cursor_manager scan --workspace <code-workspace> --json`
2. `python -m ai.agent.cursor_manager promote --workspace … --items …:mcp_file:mcp.json,workspace:mcp_workspace:workspace-mcp --on-collision overwrite --yes`
3. Remove duplicate `.cursor/mcp.json` from project mirrors once user-global config is verified.

Cursor Manager sync inventory: `user.mcp` → `~/.cursor/mcp.json`.
